Text.Value: I'll decide that for myself.
From now on, these fangs seek enemy flesh only.
Nice try.
Darling, I revel in my mysteries. You can take them from my even colder, deader hands.
Well yeah. If you were a proper vampire, you wouldn't be trudging through the mud with muggins over here.
What gave me away?
Getting caught red-fanged hasn't humbled you much, I see.
Well, well, well. A vampire in our very camp.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Character saw Astarion use his 'bite' ability on someone else (probably in combat, but not necessarily) and confronts him about being a vampire.

Text.Value: I can live with that.
Should Astarion's eyes betray even a slight hunger for gith blood, I will tear off his head before those fangs can scrape my flesh.
If you're sure about that, then I'm sure about you.
Fair enough. But I hope you know by now that I'm on your side. Anyone tries to hurt you, and they'll have to answer to the big mad furnace.
Keep your secrets if you want. But you may not have someone to tell them to if you keep it up.
You're a bad liar. Strange, for a vamp. Your kind usually sweat charm.
You bit me. No one bites me without my say-so.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Character was bitten by Astarion in gameplay.
EditorData.logicalname: WAS BITTEN BY AST IN GAMEPLAY

Text.Value: So you're a vampire, then. I had my suspicions.
What more can I say than 'thank you'.
Though I suppose Astarion feeding on Karlach is akin to a lone mosquito supping on a prize draft horse - it'll be a while before he can do any real damage.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'it's not ideal, but Karlach's probably strong enougn to lose a little blood to Astarion'

Text.Value: Look, if you don't trust me, that's on you. I've been straightforward this whole time. About who I am, about what I need.
I haven't the faintest idea what you mean.
You're lucky I can handle your bullshit.
You're very annoying. But I'm sure you know that.

EditorData.NodeContext: Like talkign to a little brother. Not angry-angry but annoyed.

Text.Value: So long as none of us are on the pointed end of his hunger pangs, I think he deserves a chance.
Impressed with myself. I slept like a baby, even after your little display.

EditorData.NodeContext: teasing astarion, but with an edge

Text.Value: Why didn't you tell me sooner?
So long as none of us are on the pointed end of Astarion's hunger pangs, I think he deserves a chance.
I have hunted spawn as the Blade. Driven by agonising hunger, every last one.
Don't think I won't. Darling.

EditorData.NodeContext: A semi flirt, semi threaten with Astarion, who's just called her darling.

Text.Value: You're too generous, Karlach. Better hope he hasn't acquired a taste for you.
I hope last night's little display was a one-time thing.
You're welcome.

EditorData.logicalname: Check more than one party member

Text.Value: New day ahead of us. Let's put this knew knowledge to good use in the fight against evil.
If that were true, you wouldn't have been feeding in our camp!
I've trusted the wrong person before. I wanted to be sure about you.
Don't patronise me, tiefling.
I guess I can't blame you for being cautious. If anything, it proves you're a good ally.
Make a meal of anyone I call 'friend', Astarion - and they will be your last. That is my solemn promise.
Did you really think you could hide what you are from me forever, vampire?

EditorData.NodeContext: ambiguous. player shouldn't know whetehr she's going to react well or badly.

Text.Value: You're being rather philosophical about all this, Karlach. I was expecting a more heated response.
You're too generous, Karlach. Better hope he hasn't acquired a taste for you.
I swear - I'm not what you think.
No more secrets, all right? We're in this together-together.
I have to be able to trust you too, you know. No more secrets, all right?
We can't help who we are. Or what's been done to us. All we have is what we do now. And from what I can tell, you're sound enough for me.
It shouldn't come as a surprise that I'd keep it under wraps for my own safety.
Make a meal of anyone I call 'friend', Astarion - and they will be your last. That is my solemn promise.
Sometimes I think I'd sleep through the apocalypse.
I have hunted spawn as the Blade. Driven by agonising hunger, every last one.
My old master forbid me from telling people what I am.
I'm on your side - I promise!
Should his eyes betray even a slight hunger for gith blood, I will tear off his head before those fangs can scrape my flesh.
No more secrets. At least no important ones.
You show the bloodsucker more mercy than he deserves, Karlach.
I had my suspicions. Which you proved all-too-right.
What didn't? If I asked a kid to draw a picture of a vampire, they'd come up with you.

EditorData.NodeContext: bit of sarcasm. astarion asked how Karlach knew

Text.Value: Sure, in the beginning, but this isn't the beginning anymore, is it?
He sounds like a real prick. Well listen, Astarion - they aren't here now. And if they should their ugly face, I'll crack it open. All right?
Well, technically, I'm a vampire spawn.
The vampire wakes.
Lucky for you, I'm very forgiving of mistakes.
You show the bloodsucker far more compassion than he deserves, Karlach.
All right, Astarion. It's time we had the talk.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Companion confronts Avatar Astarion, telling him they know he's a vampire. Triggers if you make it to Act 2 without him telling you himself or revealing it via camp night bite scene/using bite attack in front of you.
